Class Video

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Widget
      • org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Control

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, org.eclipse.rap.rwt.Adaptable, org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Drawable, org.eclipse.swt.internal.SerializableCompatibility
    public class Video
extends org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Composite

    A Video can be used to play videos from an URL on a mobile device. It provides facilities to control the video from the server side and to receive notification when the client controls will be triggered.

    Since:
    0.7
    See Also:
    PlaybackListener, Serialized Form

      • clearCache

        public void clearCache()
        Instructs the device to remove all cached content from the video cache.

        The call is asynchronous, the files are not removed immediately upon returning.

        Since:
        1.4.9

      • setSpeed

        public void setSpeed​(float speed)
        Set the playback speed. A positive value of 1.0 plays forward at normal speed. A negative value plays backward. A value of 0.0 pauses.
        Since:
        1.4.9
        See Also:
        PLAY_SPEED, PAUSE_SPEED

      • stepToTime

        public void stepToTime​(float seconds)
        Steps to a specific point in time of the video to play.
        Parameters:
        seconds - Seconds before decimal point; milliseconds after decimal point. If the argument is too large, the play position will be moved to the end of the video. If the argument is too small, the play position will be moved to the start of the video.
        Since:
        1.4.9

      • skipFromCurrent

        public void skipFromCurrent​(float seconds)
        Skip forward or backward from the current playback position. Will be affected by latency.
        Parameters:
        seconds - Seconds before the decimal point; milliseconds after the decimal point. A positive value skips forward; a negative value skips backward. If the argument is too large, the play position will be moved to the end of the video. If the argument is too small, the play position will be moved to the start of the video.
        Since:
        1.4.9
